use of period before and after quotation mark there is a third alternative to choosing either british or north american convention as nicole b said that is 'all signs of punctuation used with words in quotation marks should be placed according to logic' examples bilbo said 'we must find the wizard ' here the full stop is inside the q marks because the word wizard is the logical end of bilbo's sentence but thorin was sure that bilbo had not said 'we must find the wizard' what he had said was 'we must follow the wizard' here in both sentences the full stop is outside the q marks because the sentences ending with the word wizard are both logically about thorin's thoughts The Hobbit Punctuation Gandalf American and British English differences Full stop Quotation mark Exclamation mark The Fellowship of the Ring Russian orthography Bracket Apostrophe (mark) Dwarves (Middle-earth) Dash Ellipsis Korean language Bilbo Baggins Esperanto orthography Thorin Oakenshield Logic The Wizard of Oz (1939 film) Romanian language Question mark Timeline of Arda Abbreviation The Lord of the Rings Frodo Baggins If and only if Philosophy of language Arabic alphabet Meaning Comma (punctuation) HTML element Saruman The Return of the King F__li and K__li Existence Battle of Five Armies Self-reference The Hobbit (1977 film) The Lord of the Rings (1978 film) The Quest of Erebor Lonely Mountain Subjunctive mood Translation Baggins family Weapons of Middle-earth Vacuous truth Logical conjunction Willard Van Orman Quine Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Colon (punctuation) Middle-earth Theodore G. Bilbo Wizard Balin (Middle-earth) Smaug Dinosaur Comics Bag End Slash (punctuation) Quotation A. E. van Vogt Prolog Mithril Ludwig Wittgenstein Saul Kripke Hogwarts Second-order logic History of logic Acronym and initialism Maze Gimli (Middle-earth) Gollum International Phonetic Alphabet Religion Debate Tilde Japanese writing system Chapters and verses of the Bible Expert system Sudoku Magical obje